The paper proposes a formal model for distributed systems based on contract-oriented computing and session types. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper borrows concepts and results from the session type literature, which suggests that it may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper also discusses progress and session fidelity, which are concepts related to logic and verification, suggesting that it may belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the synthesis of choreographies, which is a topic related to systems and control, suggesting that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
